[Interested readers should access the original text via the source URL above to view the entire text, figures, tables, and references cited.

These findings are reassuring in that they are consistent with the interpretation that all diagnosed human cases of vCJD have been caused by the same agent responsible for the outbreak of bovine spongiform encephalopathy in the UK beginning in 1996, and that the agents responsible for all known cases of the disease did not originate as independent events. - Mod.CP]

